Capabilities

Wastage in Site Mixing : Cement spillage, short-ages in qunatity of aggregate and sand during delivery, storage and mixing at site, leftover aggregates after completion of concreting results.

All these wastage are avoided with Geomix as it takes care of all ingredients and the ready-to-use product is delivered at the site.

Wastage of concrete during handling:Spilage during transporting from the mixer to the point of placing is unavoidable and results in approx 0.5-o.7% Wastage.

Geomix facilates pumping of concrete to the point of placing and hence there is no wastage due to spillage etc. The leftover concrete in pump-hopper can be used for site casting.

Manpower Saving:For proportioning, mixing, transportation, placing, cpmpaction and finishing a lot of manpower is required. The manpower increases with the increase in the number of floors.

Geomix requires minimal manpower(for compaction and finishing only). Manpower and infrastructure requirements will be the same irrespective of the number of floors.

Time Saving:A lot of tine required for concreting operations and the output is very low (2-3m3/hr), thus prolonging construction time.

Geomix delivers large quantities of concrete through transit at short intervals, increasing the output manifold (15-20 m3/hr), thus reducing construction time considerably.

Savings in HouseKeeping Cost:Site mixing involves cost and time for continuous cleaning and houseKeeping operations.

Geomix virtually eliminates all houseKeepin and cleaning operations.

Space Saving:Site mix concrete consumes lots of space to store cement, aggregate, sand, water, mixing equipment etc.

Geomix delivers the ready -to use product and requires no extra storage space at the site.

Savings in Testing Cost:High cost(20-22/m3) is involved in testing of ingredients as well as concrete in fresh and hardened state.

Geomix takes care of total testing of concrete supplied including raw materials in our own laboratory.

Mixing quality:Site mixing of aggregates includes improper mixing techniques resulting in material loss and inferior quality.

Geomix takes care of the whole process by computer automated mechanisms.

Product Information

Ordinary

  • M10 : PCC (Plain Cement Concrete) e.g Leveling course, bedding for footing, concrete roads etc.
  • M15 : PCC e.g Leveling course, bedding for footing, concrete roads etc.
  • M25 :RCC (Reinforced Cement Concrete) e.g slabs, beams, column footings etc (for mild exposure).

Standard

  • M25 :RCC (Reinforced Cement Concrete) e.g slabs, beams, column footings etc.
  • M30: RCC e.g slabs, beams, columns, footings.
  • M35: RCC e.g slabs, beams, columns, footings
  • M40: RCC e.g Pre-stressed concrete, slabs, beams, columns, footings.
  • M45: RCC e.g Runways, Concrete Roads(PQC), Pre-stressed concrete Griders, RCC columns, Spans Prestressed Beams.
  • M50: RCC e.g Runways, Concrete Roads(PQC), Pre-stressed concrete Griders, RCC columns, Spans Prestressed Beams.
  • M55: RCC e.g Pre-stressed concrete Griders and Piers
  • M60: RCC work where high compressive strength is required as high rise.

High Strength

  • M25 :RCC work where high compressive strength is required as high rise buildings, long span bridges, ultra-thin white topping etc. and aggressive environment e.g Spillways of dams, Coastal construction.

Special Application Concretes

Fly Ash Concrete

  • A percentage of cement is replaced with fly ash
  • Can be used in ligt/mild structures such as raft foundations, roads pavements etc.

Early strength Concrete

  • Preffered for its early setting and compressive strength.
  • is used in construction that requires high initial strength for early form work removal.

Corrosian Resistant concrete

  • Provides protection against corrosion of steel reinforcement. Saves cost involved in providing pre coating to steel bars and concrete surface.
  • Mainly used in pile foundations, foundation for bridges across river/sea, RCC in underground conditions.

Self Compacting Concrete

  • High fluidity or viscosity with high load carrying capacity. Enables faster construction, better surface finish, easier placing, no vibration required.
  • Man power for placement is greatly reduced.

Fiber Reinforced Concrete

  • Polypropylrnr fiber is added to concrete during batching, fibers are dispersed throughout the concrete during the mixing process.
  • Used in heavy industrial floors, bridges, water retaining structure etc. improve concrete's resistance to plastic shrinkage cracking. Increase load bearing capacity of concrete. Can replace steel reinforcement for ligt/medium RCC slabs resting on ground application.

Colored Concrete

  • Wide variety of colors and textures offered. Concrete for parking areas, pavements, foot path, drive ways, gardens etc.

Water-proof Concrete

  • Used in terraces, basements, water contact structures etc

We aim to provide best quality of ready mix concrete and other construction materials.
